cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a technique for efficiently computing the Hessian of any function that is computed using a computational graph, which is a common approach in machine learning. Additionally, the paper provides experiments on neural networks, which are a popular application of machine learning. 

The paper could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a technique for computing the Hessian that can be applied to neural networks. 

Computer vision (cs.CV) is another possible sub-category as neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks, and the paper provides experiments on neural networks. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is a broad sub-category that could also be applicable as the paper proposes a technique for efficiently computing the Hessian of any function, which could have applications beyond machine learning. 

Finally, data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on developing new data structures or algorithms, but rather on a technique for computing the Hessian.
